      "span_text": "Interestingly, a recent study using a different species of relapsing fever, B. turicatae, found clearance in TLR2 Ϫ/Ϫ mice and incidence of vestibular disease to be similar to that seen with infected scid mice [CITATION_1] . This difference in TLR2 requirement in host defense could reflect differences in target tissues of these two distinct but related organisms."
